           (3CPRNIX) Zepeng Wu.
           (4AZRAZR) Innovation and Digital Development Agency
            Nuclear Research Department, Gobu str. 20th km of
            Baku-Shamakhi Highway, AZ0100, Baku, Azerbaijan.
            G.Ahmadov.
           (4KASAFU) A.K.Bekbayev,B.Mukhametuly,E.S.Korshikov,
            E.B.Myrzabekova,Y.Arynbek.
FACILITY   (VDG,4ZZZDUB) EG-5 Van de Graaff accelerator of the
           Frank Laboratory of Neutron Physics
INC-SOURCE (D-D) Deuterium gas target of 2.0 cm length,
           1.0 cm diameter, pressure 2.0 - 2.5 atm.
           The deuteron beam current ~ 2.0 microA.
           A steel collimator ( 20 x 20 x 20 cm) with a copper
           insert was used to reduce the background from scattered
           and thermal neutrons.
INC-SPECT   Quasi-monoenergetic neutrons.
            Energy resolution of the source is estimated to
            be 150-200 keV because of deuteron energy spread and
            target pressure.
SAMPLE     (3-LI-6,ENR=0.905)
           All samples were prepared on 0.10 mm thick tantalum
           backings of 48 mm diameter.
           Lithium fluoride (6LiF) samples enriched (90.5 %) in
           6Li, with varying thicknesses -
           I.   272.9 mug/cm2 for forward direction,
           II.  233.5 mug/cm2 for backward direction,
           III. 105.3 mug/cm2 for foreground measurement at
            forward and backward direction,
           IV.  46.0 mug/cm2 for foreground measurement at
            forward and backward direction.
            238U(3)O(8) 475.0 mug/cm2 thickness - for neutron flux
            measurement.
            Ta sample for background measurement.
PART-DET   (A,T) Detection of the number of alpha particles,
           tritons, and combined alpha-triton events.
           The total yield of charged particles from the
           6Li(n,t)4He reaction was obtained as the sum of the
           three identified event groups.
METHOD     . Alpha sources were used for energy calibration.
           .  Six measurement series :
            Series Collimator Working gas pressure Sample
            1      Yes         0.7 atm             I, II
            2      Yes         4.0 atm             I, II
            3      No         1.0 atm              III, IV
            4      No         1.0 atm              III, IV
            5      No         4.0 atm              III, IV
            6      No         4.0 atm              III, IV
           Altogether there were 12 measurements (6 series x
           2 configurations of samples).
           . Determination of the number of detected alpha
           particles, tritons, and combined alpha-triton events
           were done.
DETECTOR   (IOCH) Gridded ionization chamber filled with gas
            (Kr + 3% CO(2)) at variable pressure ( 0.7, 1.0,
            4.0 atm)
            For neutron flux monitoring  - two high-purity
            (99.999%) 238U(3)O(8) samples of 475.0 mug/cm2
            thickness placed inside the ionization chamber.
            Anode and cathode signals from the IOCH were
            processed by a Pixie-16 digital data acquisition
            system (14-bit resolution,250 MHz sampling rate)
            consisting of a PXI-6023 XIA-14 chassis (Wiener),
            NI PXI-8820 embedded controller, Pixie-16 high-speed
            digitizer.
           (LONGC) 3He long counter as secondary monitor to
           confirm measurement by 238U reaction.
ANALYSIS   The neutron energy was determined using kinematic
           calculations from the DD reaction.
CORRECTION  A background measurement was conducted for 2 hr using
           a pure tantalum backing.
ERR-ANALYS      Source of uncertainty :
           (ERR-1) 238U(n,f) reference cross section         0.7 %
           (ERR-2) Determination of number of fission events 3.0 %
           (ERR-3,3.0,5.0) Alpha/triton event statistics 3.0-5.0 %
           (ERR-4) Background subtraction and neutron flux
           normalization                                     3.0 %
           (ERR-5) Atoms number of 238U in the 238U(3)O(8) sample
                                                             2.0 %
           (ERR-6) Atoms number of 6Li in the 6LiF sample    2.0 %
           (ERR-T) Total combined uncertainty            7.5-9.8 %
COMMENT    Of authors in the article.
           This work was supported by the Committee of Science of
           the Ministry of Science and Higher Education of the
           Republic of Kazakhstan (BR21881930) and the National
           Natural Science Foundation of China (12475299).
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by the author E.Sansarbayar
HISTORY    (20260406C) M.M.
