BIB                  7         25
REACTION   (3-LI-6(N,T)2-HE-4,,SIG)
MONITOR    (92-U-238(N,F),,SIG) From ENDF/B-VIII.
ANALYSIS    Cross-section was determined by formula (1) in
            J,CPH/C,49,124004,2025.
            C-S is equal to sum of two parts - MISC1 + MISC2.
MISC-COL   (MISC1) Part of cross section determined via
                    alpha + (alpha+triton).
           (MISC2) Part of cross section determined via triton.
FLAG       (1.) Collimator, 6LiF thickness 272.9 mug/cm2, 1st run.
           (2.) Collimator, 6LiF thickness 272.9 mug/cm2, 2nd run.
           (3.) No collimator, 6LiF thickness 105.3 mug/cm2.
           (4.) No collimator, 6LiF thickness 46.0 mug/cm2.
COMMENT     Of the author E.Sansarbayar.
            The repeated 272.9 mug/cm2 lines in Table 4 correspond
            to two separate forward measurements with Sample I
            because the chamber was not rotated in the first two
            measurement series. Sample I was measured forward
            twice.
            Sample II (233.5 mug/cm2) was used only in the
            backward direction to verify forward-only emission (se
            Figure 4b of the article).
            In series 3-6 (with Samples III and IV), Samples were
            used in both forward and backward directions.
STATUS     (TABLE,,Yu.M.Gledenov+,J,CPH/C,49,124004,2025) Table 4
